name: Paul Kent
summary: NRL journalist Paul Kent has been stood down from his roles at Fox Sports and The Daily Telegraph pending an investigation into an alleged street fight in Sydney's Rozelle. The incident, which was captured on video, shows Kent involved in a physical altercation with another man outside a pub. Police are investigating the matter and Kent has reportedly been seen in footage of the fight. This is not the first time Kent has been involved in controversy; he was previously cleared of domestic violence charges in May.

name: Rafael Nadal
summary: Rafael Nadal's victory over Darwin Blanch at the Madrid Open has garnered significant attention. The match showcased Nadal's enduring prowess and set up a rematch with Alex de Minaur. However, concerns linger about Nadal's fitness ahead of the French Open. Despite his triumph, the Australian Open has been criticized as "unspeakably horrendous." Nadal's participation in the Laver Cup in Berlin 2024 has been confirmed, while de Minaur has expressed frustration after losing to Nadal. Nadal aims to cherish his return to red clay, with his sights set on the Olympics. The news of Novak Djokovic's withdrawal has also impacted Nadal's preparation, leaving him with doubts about his ability to prevail against de Minaur.

name: Indonesia earthquake
summary: Indonesia has experienced multiple significant earthquakes in recent hours. A magnitude 6.1 earthquake struck Java Island, causing tremors felt in Jakarta. Strong earthquakes also shook Japan, prompting authorities to warn residents of potential aftershocks. Across Indonesia, a magnitude 6.5 earthquake struck off Java Island, prompting an absence of tsunami alerts. The Sarajevo Times reported a stronger earthquake hitting Indonesia, with a magnitude of 6.5. Firstpost confirmed a 6.5-magnitude earthquake. Authorities in Java reported a magnitude 6.5 earthquake off the coast of the island. The Times of India also reported the magnitude 6.5 earthquake near Java.
